Package uniol.apt.analysis.cycles.lts

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ComputeSmallestCycles
    This class computes smallest cycles and parikh vectors, checking if all smallest cycles having the same parikh vector, or having the same or mutually disjoint parikh vectors.
    Cycle
    Representation of a cycle as a list of nodes and the Parikh vector of the edges.
    CycleCounterExample
    Datastructure for storing two counterexamples for the module.
    CyclePV
    Representation of a cycle as its Parikh vector.
    CyclesHaveSameOrMutallyDisjointPVModule
    This module checks whether all smallest cycles of a lts have same or mutually disjoint Parikh vectors
    CyclesHaveSamePVModule
    This module checks whether all smallest cycles of an lts or pn have same Parikh vectors.
    PrimeCycleProperty
    This class checks if the given lts fulfills the prime cycles property.
    PrimeCyclePropertyModule
    This module checks if the given lts fulfills the prime cycles property.
    PVsOfSmallestCyclesModule
    This module computes Parikh vectors of smallest cycles of a lts.
